world.bentobox.bentobox.api.user

Class User

  • java.lang.Object
    • world.bentobox.bentobox.api.user.User

  • public class User
extends Object
    Combines Player, OfflinePlayer and CommandSender to provide convenience methods related to localization and generic interactions.
    Therefore, a User could usually be a Player, an OfflinePlayer or the server's console. Preliminary checks should be performed before trying to run methods that relies on a specific implementation.

    It is good practice to use the User instance whenever possible instead of Player or CommandSender.
    Author:
    tastybento

        public int getPermissionValue(String permissionPrefix,
                              int defaultValue)
        Get the maximum value of a numerical permission setting. If a player is given an explicit negative number then this is treated as "unlimited" and returned immediately.
        Parameters:

        defaultValue - the default value; the result may be higher or lower than this

        max value
